    <titleInfo>
        <title>Emerging production systems in the
            transnationalisation of German carmakers</title>
        <subTitle>Adaptation,
            application or innovation?</subTitle>
    </titleInfo>
    <typeOfResource>text</typeOfResource>
    <abstract>Based on case studies, this article seeks to determine whether or not German carmakers are exporting a German production model to overseas plants and to what extent the overseas operations have a reciprocal effect on production methods in the originating country. It is argued that the most adequate analytical concept is one that emphasizes interest-driven organizational learning processes.</abstract>
